To solve this problem you could reinitialize `logcaptor` before each test:

    @SpringBootTest
    public class AppIT {
    
    	private LogCaptor logcaptor;
    
    	@Autowired
    	private FooService fooService;
    
    	@BeforeEach
    	void beforeEach() {
    		logcaptor = LogCaptor.forClass(FooService.class);
    	}
    
    	@Test
    	void testMethod() {
    		fooService.hello();
    		assertThat(logcaptor.getErrorLogs()).containsExactly(&quot;Expected error message&quot;);
    	}
    }

PS: Note that after a `logcaptor` reinitialization it will not contain previous log events.

PPS: It is better to keep a `logcaptor` non-static, so it could be garbage-collected after a test-class run.

